committer Konform Browser <https://codeberg.org/konform-browser> 1774681000 +0000

    Bug 1973598 - Move from UniquePtr to std::unique_ptr r=glandium
    
    std::unique_ptr and UniquePtr have very similar interfaces, but the
    latter is a standard container and it turns out it leads to slightly
    denser code:
    
    This saves around 50kB on a stripped libxul, with a very nice diff:
    
            61 insertions(+), 318 deletions(-)
    
    It currently uses a type alias to avoid major rewrite.
    
    Changes implied by this move:
    
    - some inner types use different naming convention
    - some definition are no longer found through ADL (because we switch
      from mozilla to std namespace)
    - ContentParentKeepAliveDeleter no longer have a nasty implicit
      dependency on UniquePtr setting the managed pointer to null before
      being called.
    - No type guide because we use a template alias
    - extra wildcard added for unique_ptr subnamespace in layout/style/ServoBindings.toml
    
    Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D255423

